00:00:00.200 --> 00:00:04.399
We're asked to multiply and express as a simplified rational.

00:00:04.399 --> 00:00:08.297
So when you multiply any rational expressions, it's just like multiplying any fractions.

00:00:08.297 --> 00:00:11.796
You multiply the numerators times each other, and the denominators times each other.

00:00:11.796 --> 00:00:14.779
So if we multiply the numerators here, and when you multiply--

00:00:14.779 --> 00:00:18.378
When you're just multiplying a bunch of numbers, it doesn't matter what order you do them in.

00:00:18.378 --> 00:00:20.479
So we want to multiply in an order that makes it a little bit clearer.

00:00:20.479 --> 00:00:22.713
We can multiply the coefficients first.

00:00:22.713 --> 00:00:25.249
We can multiply 3 times 14.

00:00:25.249 --> 00:00:27.916
3 times 14 gives us

00:00:27.916 --> 00:00:29.832
-3 times 10 is thirty-

00:00:29.832 --> 00:00:31.781
-3 times 4 is 12-

00:00:31.781 --> 00:00:33.965
It gives us 42.

00:00:33.965 --> 00:00:36.765
So that's the 3 and the 14.

00:00:36.765 --> 00:00:41.748
Then we have an a-squared, 42a-squared.

00:00:41.748 --> 00:00:45.632
Then we have a b.

00:00:45.632 --> 00:00:48.116
I'll write these in the order that the letters in the alphabet-- alphabetical order.

00:00:48.116 --> 00:00:51.799
And then we have an x-squared -and then we have an x-squared.

00:00:51.799 --> 00:00:55.348
So I just changed the order, but I just multiplied all of these things in both numerators.

00:00:55.348 --> 00:00:58.081
That's the numerators multiplied.

00:00:58.081 --> 00:00:59.899
Let's do the same thing for the denominators.

00:00:59.899 --> 00:01:03.490
So I'll first do the constant -or I should say the coefficients-

00:01:03.490 --> 00:01:06.116
I'll multiply 2 times 18, which is 36.

00:01:06.116 --> 00:01:12.167
And then I have an a over here - just one a- 36a

00:01:12.167 --> 00:01:16.984
Then I have a just one b over here -times b-

00:01:16.984 --> 00:01:21.250
Then I just have one x over here -times x-

00:01:22.173 --> 00:01:25.682
So we've multiplied the two, and now we just need to simplify them.

00:01:25.682 --> 00:01:28.237
Let's just think about this a little bit.

00:01:28.237 --> 00:01:30.770
Both 42 and 36 are divisible by 6.

00:01:30.770 --> 00:01:32.487
That's their greatest common divisor.

00:01:32.487 --> 00:01:33.986
Let's divide both of them by 6.

00:01:33.986 --> 00:01:36.738
42 divided by 6 is 7.

00:01:36.738 --> 00:01:39.422
36 divided by 6 is 6.

00:01:40.591 --> 00:01:43.844
Both a-squared and a are divisible by a, so let's divide them both by a.

00:01:43.844 --> 00:01:46.396
a-squared divided by a is a.

00:01:46.396 --> 00:01:48.895
a divided by a is one.

00:01:48.895 --> 00:01:50.664
And just remember, I'm just dividing in both

00:01:50.664 --> 00:01:54.812
--in any of these steps I'm just dividing the numerator and the denominator by the same number.

00:01:54.812 --> 00:01:57.862
And that's not changing the overall value of the expression.

00:01:59.216 --> 00:02:01.443
Then I have a b divided by a b

00:02:01.443 --> 00:02:04.526
-well I can divide the numerator and the denominator by b-

00:02:05.711 --> 00:02:09.551
And so, those two characters will cancel out.

00:02:09.551 --> 00:02:11.801
To just 1 and 1.

00:02:11.801 --> 00:02:13.751
You don't even have to write it when you multiply by 1.

00:02:13.751 --> 00:02:15.018
It doesn't change the value.

00:02:15.018 --> 00:02:16.968
And then I have an x-squared divided by x.

00:02:16.968 --> 00:02:18.468
They're both divisible by x.

00:02:18.468 --> 00:02:20.551
x-squared divided by x is x.

00:02:20.551 --> 00:02:22.951
x divided by x is 1.

00:02:22.951 --> 00:02:29.236
So, in the numerator we are left with 7ax.

00:02:29.236 --> 00:02:32.002
We can ignore the b, because it's just multiplying by 1 now.

00:02:32.002 --> 00:02:36.301
We have 7 -let me do that same shade of green-

00:02:37.947 --> 00:02:44.324
